Abia State Governor, Okezie Ikpeazu has approved the immediate dissolution of the Abia State Local Government Service Commission. This was contained in a terse statement issued to DAILY POST by the Secretary to the State Government, SSG, Barrister Chris Ezem, on Saturday. According to the statement, the Governor ”thanks all the former members of the Commission for their services and wishes them well in their future endeavors”. Abia: Gov Ikpeazu gives update on salary payment Abia Gov Ikpeazu suspends his Chief of Staff Gov Ikpeazu to commission more road projects, Friday